							consumption </a>
					</h4>
				</div>
				<div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse"
					role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingThree">
					<div class="panel-body">
						<img class="img-responsive img-rounded center-block" alt="Alcohol"
							src="http://www.businesstoday.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/alcohol-bar.jpg">
						<br>
						<p align="justify">
						Good news, you don't need to stop drinking alcohol
						completely. The effects of alcohol on one's health are presented
						in a J-shape or U-shape as they like to call it. This means that
						consuming to much alcohol has negative effects on your wellbeing,
						but complete abstinence also seems not warranted. Or in other
						words, moderate alcohol consumption can be good for your health.
						When we talk about moderate consumption we need to make some
						things clear. First you need to know what is meant with
						"moderate". This is defined in many ways, but generally taken it
						comes down to this:
						<ul>
							<li>Max. 2 units per day for men and 1 unit per day for
								women. With units, the normal serving portions are meant.</li>
							<li>In total no more than 14 units per week for men and 7
								units per week for women. You cannot consume 14 units in one
								day.</li>
						</ul>
						<p align="justify">
						Another issue is the "consumption pattern". The best pattern seems
						to be when you drink the allowed amount of alcohol every single
						day again. It is this continuous consumption pattern that is
						associated with the greatest health benefits. Drinking large
						amounts of alcohol in a short period of time, like the youngsters
						partying in the weekend, does not seem to be a great idea and even
						has detrimental effects on health. A third point of concern
						applies to the "kind of beverage" you drink. Not all alcoholic
						drinks result in health benefits when consumed moderately and
						regularly. Strong liquors for example do not contribute to your
						health. Beers and white wine only have moderate effects. The
						greatest effect is achieved by drinking red wine. The mechanisms
						are contributable to two substances present in these beverages.
						They are called polyphenols and resveratrol. These 2 substances
						are abundantly present in red wine. Lastly, in some patient groups
						(e.g. atrial fibrillation or when taking some kinds of medication)
						drinking alcohol can stay absolutely contra-indicated. <b>Always
							consult your general practitioner when in doubt!</b>


					</div>
				</div>
